WEBVTT

00:00:01.588 --> 00:00:04.588
Remote Desktop Protocol Attack 
with Crowbar

00:00:04.833 --> 00:00:09.865
Crowbar is a network authentication 
cracking tool primarily designed 

00:00:09.865 --> 00:00:13.566
to leverage SSH keys rather 
than passwords.

00:00:13.566 --> 00:00:17.988
It’s also one of the few tools that can 
reliably and efficiently 

00:00:17.988 --> 00:00:19.833
perform password attacks 
 against the RDP service 

00:00:19.833 --> 00:00:23.633
on modern versions of Windows.

00:00:23.633 --> 00:00:27.366
Let’s try this tool against our Windows 
client machine.

